This would be incorporated in Reports. Suggestion courtesy of a customer:

{quote}
We aren't using Kanban strategies so we don't have much need for column limits and the like, but one thing that would be nice is if GreenHopper could automagically (I'm sure with some configuration) provide the team/managers with column metrics.  Things like average time per column (based on issue type?), and also the ability to identify bubbles on the board where issues stack up and spend long amounts of time.  We usually feel those bubbles and pain points through daily usage, but it's always nice to be able to quantify it if possible.
{quote}

The resulting stacktrace is:
{panel}
An error occurred whilst rendering this message. Please contact the administrators, and inform them of this bug. Details: ------- org.apache.velocity.exception.MethodInvocationException: Invocation of method 'getRankingBoard' in class com.pyxis.greenhopper.jira.actions.RankingAction threw exception class java.lang.ClassCastException : com.pyxis.greenhopper.jira.fields.FixForVersion cannot be cast to com.pyxis.greenhopper.jira.fields.RankingField at org.apache.velocity.runtime.parser.node.ASTIdentifier.execute(ASTIdentifier.java:183) at ....
